******
[2] Gujarat: fatal case
Date: Tue 23 Aug 2016
Source: The News International [edited]
https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/144662-Congo-Virus-patient-dies-in-Rawalpindi


A young patient, diagnosed with Congo virus [Crimean Congo hemorrhagic fever], died [Tue 23 Aug 2016] in a local hospital [in Rawalpindi] after having remained admitted therein for 4 days.

Sources said that the victim, aged 35, was a resident of Gujarat and was shifted to Rawalpindi on [19 Aug 2016].

He was under treatment in Fouji Foundation Hospital, Gujarat where he was diagnosed with Congo virus. The body has been handed over to his relatives after medico legal formalities.

It is worth mentioning here that there are almost 10 patients under treatment in different hospitals of Rawalpindi who have been diagnosed with Congo fever.

